        <name>Astrogrid Workbench</name>
        <description>
	 	The Workbench is a suite of client-side components for accessing AstroGrid services - a registry browser,
		myspace manager, job controller and application invoker. It is layered upon the AstroGrid Client Runtime (ACR).
                
                The (ACR) is a desktop service which other client-side applications can connect with
                to interact with astrogrid. At present the ACR provides HTTP / XML-RPC / Gui interfaces to astrogrid client-side components.
                Plan to add Java-RMI imminently.
		
		Using the ACR expert users can write programs and scripts in the language of their choice (for example Python, Perl, Bash, C)
		that interact with AstroGrid services.
                
               The ACR provides a single sign-on, single-configuration, and single cache for interactions with astrogrid servers -
                making implementation of client-side applications simpler.
		  </description>
        <shortDescription>AstroGrid Workbench and Client Runtime</shortDescription>

        <packageGroups>
                <packageGroup>
                        <title>Astrogrid Client Runtime Public Interface</title>
                        <packages>org.astrogrid.acr*</packages>
                </packageGroup>
                <packageGroup>
                        <title>Implementation</title>
                        <packages>org.astrogrid.desktop*</packages>
                </packageGroup>
        </packageGroups>
	
        <build>
                <sourceDirectory>src/java</sourceDirectory>
                <unitTestSourceDirectory>test/java</unitTestSourceDirectory>
                <unitTest>
                        <includes>
                                <include>**/*Test.java</include>
                        </includes>
                        <resources>
                                <resource>
                                        <directory>${basedir}/test/java</directory>
                                        <includes>
                                                <include>**/*.properties</include>
                                                <include>**/*.xml</include>
                                        </includes>
                                </resource>
                        </resources>
                </unitTest>
                <resources>
                        <resource>
